The Nelspruit police are investigating a case of culpable homicide after a vehicle driven by a traffic officer hit and killed a pedestrian last Thursday. “The traffic officer was going to work when the incident took place. The police are investigating a case of culpable homicide,” said  Brig Leonard Hlathi, spokesperson for the police. He adds that a warning statement was obtained and taken to the public prosecutor for a decision. ALSO READ: Alleged hit-and-run driver identified 